# Google Cloud MCP Environment Variables Configuration

# --- OPTION 1: Use Client ID and Secret (Recommended) ---
# 1. Create an OAuth 2.0 Client ID (Desktop Application) in Google Cloud Console.
# 2. Copy and paste the values below.
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret

# --- OPTION 2: Use Credentials JSON Path ---
# 1. Download your credentials.json file.
# 2. Provide the absolute path below.
GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS_PATH=/root/PROJECTS/google-cloud-mcp/credentials.json

# --- TOKEN PATH (REQUIRED FOR BOTH OPTIONS) ---
# This file will be automatically generated after the first run/authentication.
# It stores your session token.
GOOGLE_TOKEN_PATH=/root/PROJECTS/google-cloud-mcp/token.json

# --- HOW TO GET THE TOKEN ---
# 1. Start the server (uv run server.py).
# 2. Click the authentication link provided in the console.
# 3. Log in with your Google account and grant permissions.
# 4. Copy the URL from the redirected (error) page and paste the 'code' parameter back into the console.
# 5. The 'token.json' will be created at the path specified above.
